The article discusses the importance of Dreamers, individuals who were brought to the United States as children, and their contributions to the nation. It highlights how Dreamers serve in various roles, including frontline workers during the pandemic, students, entrepreneurs, small business owners, and military personnel. The article mentions the creation of the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals (DACA) program ten years ago, which allowed Dreamers to live and contribute to the country without the fear of deportation. The author emphasizes the need to protect Dreamers and calls on Congressional Republicans to support a bill that provides a pathway to citizenship for them. It is argued that such a move would not only be the right thing to do but also beneficial for the economy and communities.